HEADWORD: Sole
<hw>Sole</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[From <ets>hydrosol</ets> an aqueous colloidal solution, confused
with G. <ets>sole</ets>, <ets>soole</ets>, salt water from which salt is
obtained.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A fluid mixture of a colloid
and a liquid; a liquid colloidal solution or suspension.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sola</ent>⟦br⟧
